      mechanism: 'Positive allosteric modulator of GABA-A receptors: binds the α/γ subunit interface between α1, α2, α3, or α5 subunits and the γ2 subunit, increasing the frequency of Cl⁻ channel opening in response to GABA (without activating the channel in GABA\'s absence). Does not increase channel conductance or opening duration — that is the barbiturate mechanism. Active metabolites (nordiazepam, temazepam, oxazepam) extend the clinical effect; half-life of parent compound 20–100 hours.',
